      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BARDIGRUB (6) is a handy filly resuming for the R & C Jolly camp. The form around her last prep stacks right up for this and her lead-up trial suggests she's returned in great order. Expect her to bounce straight to the front and take plenty of running down. NORHEIM (4) dug deep to get off the mark when resuming at Murray Bridge. Less effective second-up over the 1100m, so could appreciate dropping back the trip this time. Milnes' booking is a good push. SKADOOSH (8) has been far from her best in her two runs back but has been freshened and trialled well in between. Willing to give another chance third-up. BREAKFAST (7) was a dominant winner when resuming last time in and shoulders peaks that measure up. Not forgetting.",
